#summary Overview of feed processing life cycle

= Feed Processing Life Cycle =

The feed processing life cycle is the defined as the feed job or feed jobs included within a completed feed life cycle that either processes the given feed file to successful completion or permanently rejects the feed file as a feed that cannot not be successfully completed.

= Feed Processing Life Cycle State Diagram =

The diagram defines the combined states of the feed file and feed a given feed job during the feed file life cycle.
